[{"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-13T16:54:16+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"An image showing the 23andMe test\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/03cJp3xqMBPL_lGTvCcHXKuDed8=/0x3:4000x2670/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73584254/1230927570.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Getty</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"F36LJT\">23andMe will pay $30 million to settle a class action lawsuit over a data breach that <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/12/4/23988050/23andme-hackers-accessed-user-data-confirmed\">affected more than 6.9 million customers</a>. As <a href=\"https://www.documentcloud.org/documents/25139395-23andme-settlement?responsive=1&amp;title=1\">part of the proposed settlement</a>, the genetic testing site will compensate affected customers and provide them with access to a security monitoring program for three years.</p>\n<p id=\"Zfd5Sp\">23andMe <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/10/19/23923861/23andme-possible-data-leak-hack\">disclosed the data breach</a> last October, but it didn\u2019t confir", "id": 1141832, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/13/24243986/23andme-settlement-dna-data-breach-lawsuit", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "23andMe agrees to pay $30 million to settle lawsuit over massive data breach", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-13T16:35:54+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"The Anker MagGo USB-C Adapter attached to an iPhone and on its own with its card slots revealed.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/sjVUwvxob9dFTP9ja8tfQVjhqew=/0x0:1250x833/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73584194/anker1.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The Anker MagGo USB-C Adapter supports both SD and microSD cards.</em> | Image: Anker</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"WzVoq9\">Anker\u2019s next <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/5/24236006/anker-3-in-1-maggo-folding-qi2-charger-power-bank-stand-magsafe\">puck-shaped accessory</a> is an SD and microSD card reader called the <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com?id=66960X1514734&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.anker.com%2Fproducts%2Fa83d1-maggo-usb-c-adapter%3Fvariant%3D44058148241558%26ref%3Dundefined_explore_the_latest_lineup&amp;referrer=theverge.com&amp;sref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2024%2F9%2F13%2F24244018%2Fanker-magnetic-card-reader-usb-c-iphone-prores-4k\" ", "id": 1141833, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/13/24244018/anker-magnetic-card-reader-usb-c-iphone-prores-4k", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Anker\u2019s new $35 MagSafe gadget sticks SD cards to your iPhone", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-13T15:14:16+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Hot Ones host Sean Evans.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/tuS1zVH2R_ApNpFkq7u3LvA4178=/300x0:3540x2160/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73584021/videoframe_34064.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: First We Feast</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"9wujnE\">Netflix is looking to bolster its live offerings with some chicken wings. <a href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-09-13/netflix-in-talks-for-hot-ones-show-to-bolster-live-tv-lineup?srnd=homepage-americas\"><em>Bloomberg</em> and</a> <a href=\"https://variety.com/2024/tv/news/netflix-hot-ones-live-shows-1236143502/\"><em>Variety</em> report</a> that Netflix is in talks with <em>BuzzFeed</em> about streaming live versions of the <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/@FirstWeFeast/featured\">popular YouTube show \u201cHot Ones,\u201d</a> which features famous people eating spicy wings while being interviewed by host Sean Evans. Netflix and <em>BuzzFeed</em> want to make a deal this", "id": 1141486, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/13/24243999/netflix-live-episodes-hot-ones", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Netflix wants to stream live episodes of Hot Ones", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-13T14:41:52+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Vector collage showing various aspects of using Threads.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Unbld2im6lM8P35CAiQin3fjBwI=/0x0:3000x2000/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73246878/HT055_THREADS_CVirginia.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"KeBFdu\">It looks like the fediverse is continuing to open up. In late March, <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/3/21/24107881/threads-fediverse-beta-launch-mastodon\">Meta\u2019s Threads introduced a beta feature</a> that allows users from the US, Canada, or Japan to cross-post and view likes from Mastodon and, presumably, other federated social networks. In June, it added that ability to <a href=\"https://www.threads.net/@zuck/post/C8pQC2Ap_7w?hl=en\">over 100 countries</a>. </p>\n<div class=\"c-float-left c-float-hang\"><aside id=\"rhvH3V\"><div data-anthem-component=\"readmore\" data-anthem-component-data='{\"stories\":[{\"title\":\"Threads\u2019 fediverse beta opens t", "id": 1141487, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24107998/threads-fediverse-mastodon-how-to", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "How to cross-post your Threads posts to the fediverse", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-13T13:45:08+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A person holding the Snappy smartphone camera grip with a phone attached to it.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/g-bkxOoTsN-mhz5accQXzwA89mo=/2x0:1100x732/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73583820/snappy1.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The Snappy grip is designed to improve the ergonomics of smartphone photography.</em> | Image: Buddiesman</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"kryWqY\">The <a href=\"https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/buddiesmanofficial/snappy-super-stable-camera-grip-and-battery-for-mobile-phones\">Snappy is another mobile grip accessory</a> attempting to improve the ergonomics of smartphone photography, but it goes one step further by adding <a href=\"https://newatlas.com/photography/snappy-smartphone-camera-mount/\">a motorized gimbal</a> for stabilization.</p>\n<p id=\"FhSNjQ\">The <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24239802/iphone-16-pro-max-hands-on-apple-photos-features-price\">Camera Control</a> on the new iPho", "id": 1141060, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/13/24243735/snappy-smartphone-photography-grip-kickstarter", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Snappy could improve smartphone photography with a stabilized grip", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-13T13:12:50+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/O93nhug-No7yLp5EiHyPfCl6xhY=/0x171:1024x854/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73583752/World_s_First_Smart_Deadbolt_With_UWB_NFC_Technology.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The Ultraloq Bolt Mission UWB Plus NFC is the first smart lock to launch that leverages ultra wideband auto-unlocking technology.</em> | Image: U-tec</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"AIOm12\">U-tec\u2019s new smart lock will allow your door to unlock automatically as you approach it using ultra wideband (UWB) technology. The auto-unlock features that U-tec and others previously offered used a <a href=\"https://support.shopyalehome.com/en_us/how-does-auto-unlock-work-r1tW8RQyD\">combination of BLE, Wi-Fi, and GPS</a>, which can be unreliable and slow. The <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com?id=66960X1514734&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fu-tec.com%2Fblogs%2Fnews%2Fthe-worlds-first-uwb-technology-in-smart-lock-application-to-surp", "id": 1140681, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/13/24243694/ultraloq-bolt-mission-uwb-matter-smart-lock-apple-home", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "This is the first smart lock to support ultra wideband ", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-13T13:11:33+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"It\u2019s a white revolver with black and orange stripes.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/O6tA-7IszbA4k0ejH7cSQt-o5HU=/0x167:1000x834/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73583750/aos_pdp_02_1000x1000.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The Destiny 2 Nerf Ace of Spades blaster.</em> | Image: Hasbro</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"PVEdb9\">When Bungie and Hasbro decided to create a <a href=\"https://bungiestore.com/bungie-rewards-nerf-ace-of-spades-blaster\">real-life, dart-blasting Nerf version</a> of one of the most famous <em>Destiny 2</em> guns, someone got lazy \u2014 stealing a fan artist\u2019s nine-year-old work instead of creating the Ace of Spades from scratch. </p>\n<p id=\"cI0WEV\">To Bungie\u2019s credit, the game company <a href=\"https://x.com/destiny2team/status/1834627335494185335?s=46&amp;t=s7yjJ2YTk92nj3NQJLk0ww\">has just announced</a> it will \u201cmake sure\u201d to compensate and credit Tofu Rabbit \u201cfor their incredible artwork,\u201d after a rapid ", "id": 1140682, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/13/24243893/destiny-2-nerf-ace-of-spades-stole-artists-work", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Bungie will compensate an artist after its Destiny 2 Nerf blaster ripped off their work", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-13T12:55:45+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/9DTiLnzzEDOiSILShkfh6M4CZlM=/0x51:1179x837/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73583681/GXVIIN2bgAAhB7w.5.jpeg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>This photo, from X user </em><a class=\"ql-link\" href=\"https://x.com/MatthewDR/status/1834451732459651206\" target=\"_blank\"><em>@MatthewDR</em></a><em> via Reddit user u/boopitysmopp (since deleted), could be of Tesla\u2019s long-gestating robotaxi. </em> | Screenshot: u/boopitysmopp, <a class=\"ql-link\" href=\"https://x.com/MatthewDR/status/1834451732459651206\" target=\"_blank\">via @MatthewDR</a></figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"9Akukm\">A blurry photo of a heavily camouflaged vehicle tooling around on the Warner Bros. movie studio lot surfaced last night, spurring speculation that it\u2019s <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/3/24234785/tesla-robotaxi-event-warner-bros-mapping-data-musk\">the fabled Tesla robotaxi</a> set to be revealed next month. </p>\n<p id=\"2eGVgU\"", "id": 1140683, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/13/24243807/tesla-robotaxi-spy-shot-reddit-yellow-camo-shape", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Is this weirdly shaped, canary yellow thing Tesla\u2019s robotaxi?", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-13T11:45:00+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A still image from the film Megalopolis.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/bMbws24maX6kmVdlMAZqdCp014E=/0x0:900x600/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73583528/Megalopolis_Still_01.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Lionsgate</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>Francis Ford Coppola\u2019s long-gestating epic Megalopolis is a series of loosely connected ideas, tied together with an undercooked world and embarrassing dialogue.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24243766/megalopolis-review\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>\n\n", "id": 1140282, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24243766/megalopolis-review", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "What the hell did I just watch?", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-13T11:17:12+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Vector illustration of the Spotify logo.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/-8pYHlLEzZO7I4GdBvu1ccWeYHk=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73583473/STK088_SPOTIFY_CVIRGINIA_D.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Cath Virginia / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"spuQLH\">If kids are asking to hear one song from <em>Encanto</em> on repeat, it can filter back into the algorithm and recommendations for a parent\u2019s Spotify profile. The company tried addressing the issue with a <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2019/10/30/20938076/spotify-kids-app-announced-disney-taylor-swift-family-plan\">dedicated kids app</a>, and last year, Spotify added a feature to <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/2/8/23591289/spotify-exclude-from-your-taste-profile-playlist-made-for-you\">exclude specific playlists from your taste profile.</a></p>\n<p id=\"6Tjw8V\">Now, <a href=\"https://newsroom.spotify.com/2024-09-13/spotify-pilots-new-", "id": 1139542, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/13/24243778/spotify-managed-account-parent-child-account-controls", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Spotify is testing a new way to keep kids songs out of your listening history", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-13T10:47:04+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Close-up of the OnePlus Watch 2 on a red book\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/lFEArrv7c64kSdJGfzWQdC7Q8N0=/0x0:2700x1800/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73583407/247069_Oneplus_watch_2_AKrales_0125.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>In addition to offering a $70 discount, OnePlus is also throwing in your choice of a free strap or charging base. </em> | Photo by Amelia Holowaty Krales / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"hdM4g2\">The <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24239115/google-pixel-watch-3-review-smartwatch-wear-os-wearable\">Google Pixel Watch 3</a> is here while the new <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24236958/apple-watch-series-10-hands-on-bigger-brighter-and-thinner\">Apple Watch Series 10</a> is on its way, but they\u2019re not for everybody. Luckily, there is a <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23449363/best-android-smartwatches-wear-os\">wide range of excellent Android smartwatches on the market</a>, and today", "id": 1139543, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/13/24242856/oneplus-watch-2-ember-mug-2-deal-sale", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The OnePlus Watch 2, one of our top Android smartwatch picks, hits its best price", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-13T10:46:55+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Screenshot from Astro Bot featuring Astro riding a DualSense controller over a gorgeous ocean\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/hDSk3qwqQHLs6OcTpd7Ezi5rrd4=/146x0:1496x900/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73583405/53971042042_e76709bbf9_h.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Team Asobi / Sony</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"AyTF66\"><em>Astro Bot </em>is a game <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24237778/astro-bot-review-ps5-game-of-the-year\">I cannot help but to evangelize</a>, raving about its cute characters, its bright and varied level design, and its short but dense 8\u201310 hour runtime. But perhaps the biggest element contributing to the game\u2019s joyousness is its sound design, which makes <em>Astro Bot</em> something that engages and delights more than just your mind but your body as well.</p>\n<p id=\"yfk2Tb\"><em>Astro Bot</em> had me hooked before the game even started. I left my PS5 running on the game\u2019s preload screen and ", "id": 1139544, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/13/24243763/astro-bot-sound-design-dualsense-controller", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Astro Bot sounds as great as it plays", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-13T10:40:26+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A side-by-side close up of the four colors of iPhone 16 Pro phones.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/duw6WliC9dEUPC1xqpMGXmjTImk=/137x0:2438x1534/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73583397/iphone_16_pro.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Apple\u2019s higher-end iPhones feature a titanium finish and a new \u201cdesert\u201d option. (That just means dark gold.)</em> | Screenshot: Apple</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"PlsZlZ\">Apple\u2019s new <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24237940/iphone-16-hands-on-pictures-price-features-apple\">iPhone 16</a>, <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24237940/iphone-16-hands-on-pictures-price-features-apple\">16 Plus</a>, <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24239802/iphone-16-pro-max-hands-on-apple-photos-features-price\">16 Pro</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24239802/iphone-16-pro-max-hands-on-apple-photos-features-price\">16 Pro Max</a> are already <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24237057/apple-iphone-16-p", "id": 1139545, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24242170/iphone-16-vs-pro-plus-max-comparison-specs-price-apple", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "How all the new iPhone 16 models compare to one another on paper", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-13T10:35:02+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Photo collage of a photo of the US Capitol building with an image of the Constitution behind it.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/R6yY_dOeYFhWDwdh7eMl3jnSuJk=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73583389/STK481_STK432_CONGRESS_GOVERNMENT_CIVRGINIA_C.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Cath Virginia / The Verge; Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"cydVLH\">The Biden administration is addressing the \u201cde minimis\u201d exemption that it says some Chinese e-commerce companies \u201cabuse\u201d to ship products under $800 to US customers without tariffs. </p>\n<p id=\"thchjQ\">New <a href=\"https://www.w